summary: An Ordinance fixing the rate of taxes to be levied and levying the taxes upon the taxable property in the City of Seattle, both real and personal, needed to raise sufficient revenue to meet the expense of the different departments of the City Government of The City of Seattle, for the ensuing fiscal year, to-wit: for the year beginning on the first day of January, 1911 and ending on the 31st day of December 1911, including the interest to accrue during said year on the bonded debt of The City of Seattle.
